-- Ukraine Spring Grain Seeding Ahead of Last Year, Researcher Says
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2012-04-28T14:41:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-28/ukraine-spring-grain-seeding-ahead-of-last-year-researcher-says.html
Ukraine plantings of spring grains
is 12.4 percent ahead of last year, agriculture researcher
UkrAgroConsult said.  Plantings advanced to 4.98 million hectares (12.3 million
acres) as of yesterday, Kiev-based UkrAgroConsult said in an e-
mailed statement today. This compares with 4.43 million hectares
seeded by the same date last year, the researcher said.  Spring grain plantings this year included 2.8 million
hectares of barley, 250,000 hectares of spring wheat and other
crops, UkrAgroConsult said.  Sunflower planting rose as of yesterday to 1.46 million
hectares, compared with 372,000 hectares a year ago, the
researcher said. Soybean areas rose to 223,000 hectares from
198,000 last year, UkrAgroConsult said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
